# Quality check after every fix

Any change to draft content, illustrations, covers, or status must pass the pipeline gate again before `ready` or `published`.

## Required workflow

1. After a fix, run **`audit-one-draft.ts`** (strict by default) or **`runPublishPipelineGate(d, { strict: true })`**.
2. Strict gate = structural + cover + illustrations + **genre verify** + **dialogue/prose** (fiction/NF) or **instructional materials** (Textbooks / Education) + **climax** (fiction only).
3. Do **not** mark `ready` or publish until strict gate **passes**.
4. Follow the full cover → outline → Story Architect path for new work (see `story-pipeline-quality.mdc`). Educational books: see `educational-books-pipeline.mdc`.

## Scripts

- Single draft (strict): `npx tsx script/audit-one-draft.ts <id>`
- Promote only if pass: `npx tsx script/audit-one-draft.ts <id> --promote`
- Structural-only (exception): `npx tsx script/audit-one-draft.ts <id> --structural-only`

## User expectation

Fixing something does not mean it is done. **Fix → quality check → then ready/publish.**

If the same failure happens twice (especially connection/API errors), **stop and diagnose** — see `fail-twice-then-diagnose.mdc`. Do not keep burning API retries.
